article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 67, Lehigh 39
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- Jhamar Youngblood scored 16 points to lead Monmouth to a 67-39 win over Lehigh on Friday night. Marques Alston added 10 points and six rebounds for the Hawks (4-8), who took command early on and held double-digit leads for most of the game. John Bunch added seven points, eight rebounds and three blocks for Monmouth, while Dejan Delic finished with nine points and six assists as Monmouth made 47 percent of its shots. Marquis Hall had a game-high 18 points for the Mountain Hawks (5-10), who made just five baskets in the first half and hit only 29 percent of their shots overall. They also committed 19 turnovers as the Hawks had a dominant defensive performance. Monmouth also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding Lehigh 32-31.
